$ c datatypes
@ datatypes

rem {

`char` (`unsigned` and `signed`) contains `CHAR_BITS` (but at least 8) bits. A `char` can contain *basic characters set*.

Apparently, `short` = `short int`.

rem }

{ Sizes in bytes

  A simple c program to show the sizes of some data types in bytes:

  gh|about-c|/datatypes/sizeof.c||

}

